{"type": "article", "id": 43848, "title": "这个小圆盘，用它量什么尺寸都很容易｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-08-07T23:12:43Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 43048, "name": "United By Blue"}, {"id": 43049, "name": "Oru Kayak"}, {"id": 43050, "name": "Crux"}, {"id": 43051, "name": "Camille Kachani"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 17, "praise_count": 122, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170807180424TkKXLsCwIGHEv9Ze.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #323333} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #323333; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p5 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font-kerning: none; color: #363636} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。<br></p><h3>Rollbe by The Work of Mind</h3><p>测量不规则物体的周长时，传统的卷尺就没那么好用了。来自加拿大的设计团队 The Work of Mind 为此研发了一款名为 Rollbe 的滚尺，只要沿着物体边缘滚动，记住滚动一圈的次数相乘即可。和我们之前介绍过的滚动<a href=\"https://www.qdaily.com/articles/34330.html\">智能测量笔</a>不同，圆盘状的 Rollbe 并不能直接测量某些角落，但依然可以根据表面标注的半径计算后得出长度。它一共分为 4 英尺/10 厘米和 8 英尺/20 厘米两种尺寸，每一款都配有带钥匙圈的皮制小口袋，携带起来也相当方便。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/2107879482/rollbe-super-compact-measuring-tool\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 22 加元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180457o6cODSUqhRPIQe58.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.559375\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180458liYbOdMa5XEwhq1n.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.713235\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180456ru4KLt2wk7b8YdMh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.527941\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180457KF60NuewRgr2ah4J.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180456Ub1zPuXE59CoH0qj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.685294\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Oru Beach LT kayak by United By Blue &amp; Oru Kayak</h3><p>喜欢玩水、划船，但犯愁没地方塞下划艇？美国公司 <a href=\"https://www.orukayak.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Oru Kayak</a> 专营以折纸为灵感设计的划艇，它平时就是一个可以直接背出门的大型“公文包”，用户只要五分钟的时间就能将它展开下水。最近，户外装备品牌 <a href=\"https://unitedbyblue.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">United By Blue</a> 与 Oru Kayak 推出了合作款划艇，表面采用了密集的流线印花，可以辅助人们辨别水的流向。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.orukayak.com/products/beach-lt-kayak-ubb-collaboration\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 1299 美元，附有联名背包、帽子和 T 恤。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180535dV6g0i5XpNGCaoxZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180537gJnH0L1qPlRDXbIc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180534Wdt6T8OIVnlC30KQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.338631\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807180538geF0tkn9TzI27DoO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.727384\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Ora by Crux</h3><p>在英国产品设计公司 <a href=\"http://www.cruxproductdesign.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Crux</a> 看来，市面上现有的追踪装置不仅不够隐蔽，也很难与轻便美观联系在一起。以设计一款供所有人群使用的装置为目标，他们推出了这个名为 Ora 的小信标，它就像坠饰一样可以直接佩戴在身上。一旦用户发现自己遇到紧急情况，只要两手将 Ora 下半部分扭转 180 度就能激活警报，配套的手机应用会及时通知监护人和周围的警察。Ora 是今年红点设计奖智能设备概念类的获奖作品，它目前还处于概念设计阶段。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191823NgKvnus5w6TJlBxQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.532290\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191824pFHLX94drgBis8t1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.499537\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191824mrYkdu3ScFTN26ho.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.708333\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191823E62ILcvlfFeYnQwa.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714167\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Welcome package by Hosty Club</h3><p>为了帮助 Airbnb 的房东们向房客提供类似酒店的一次性日用品，纽约设计师 <a href=\"https://connorlee.myportfolio.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Connor Lee</a> 成立了一个名为 Hosty Club 的服务平台，让房东可以定制并订购独一无二的欢迎包，减轻添置配套设施的负担。住客欢迎包内可以放入钥匙、Wi-Fi 信息、当地指南和一次性洗漱用品，根据 Lee 的<a href=\"http://design-milk.com/hosty-club-makes-life-little-easier-airbnb-hosts/\" rel=\"nofollow\">介绍</a>，超级房东在订购时还能获得一定的折扣。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191953zOtZDsvioEqSuWUB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071919531KVeq8DwiLmAF6XO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.607407\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191953XgdKBRpU1uba3rwc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.467901\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191953xFbLwVpMlgSrO5cf.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667901\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Wooden sculptures by Camille Kachani</h3><p>你见过能体现自然生长变化的家具吗？最近，黎巴嫩艺术家 <a href=\"http://camillekachani.com.br/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Camille Kachani</a> 创作了一系列“发芽”的木雕塑，试图借此反思人与自然的关系：这些长出人造树叶的书本封面、剪刀柄、椅子显然已经不能使用了，像是试图回到它们原本的模样。目前，这些雕塑正在圣保罗的 <a href=\"http://www.zippergaleria.com.br/en/artistas/camille-kachani/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Zipper</a> 画廊展出。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071917526vDraPwX4e9Ik28L.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071917527xDsiFY43GmKjIvy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.678889\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071917529QF8lEpBAVxX2aIJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.668000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191753JErvqPfHMGNYtKnZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.930743\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071917529Nm58EojiagnpxrB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>The Connective Project by Ansel Oommen et al.</h3><p>今年七月中旬，纽约布鲁克林的展望公园（<a href=\"https://www.prospectpark.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Prospect Park</a>）内近年来被人逐渐淡忘的玫瑰花园（Rose Garden）成为了艺术项目 <a href=\"https://www.connectiveproject.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Connective Project</a> 的所在地，在艺术家 <a href=\"http://www.brooklynartscouncil.org/artists/30902\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ansel Oommen</a>、建筑师 <a href=\"https://www.reddymadedesign.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Suchi Reddy</a> 和创意公司 <a href=\"http://www.wearearea4.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">AREA4</a> 的联手策划下，占地 15 亩的草坪变成了一个由 7000 个黄色风车组成的海洋。恰逢展望公园建成 150 周年，他们希望通过这种方式让园区内的景点重焕活力。值得一提的是，有超过 1000 个风车是独一无二的定制款，纸张的另一面印有当地民众设计的图案。<br></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191854JnZfWmHK0ipQjkgs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.361111\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201708071918545lNxe3MPHwm4E0In.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191854BDzjpof3d09Flsg6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170807191855ZcT3JnAP7G20CNrh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.731051\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}